-- U.S.-based stock funds attract $3.7 billion over week-Lipper
-- By Luciana Lopez
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 05:24PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, June 5 (Reuters) - Investors in U.S.-based funds committed $3.7 billion to stock funds in the week ended June 4 after adding $2 billion to the funds the prior week, data from Thomson Reuters' Lipper service showed on Thursday.

Stock mutual funds attracted $457 million in new cash, while stock exchange-traded funds drew $3.25 billion. Stock mutual funds are commonly purchased by retail investors, while stock ETFs are thought to represent the institutional investor.